"script": "That tiny match in your hand holds a controlled explosion. First, thin sticks of wood are soaked in chemicals so they smolder slowly instead of bursting into flame. Then the tips are dunked into a paste of sulfur and a touch of powdered glass. And that glass is the trick, because when you strike it, the friction creates instant heat. Next, that heat ignites a chemical on the side of the box called red phosphorus. This means the fire isn't really in the match at all. Finally, the spark jumps across, and the whole tip erupts into flame.",
